						<summary>

						<p>West base of the verandah in the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the Mantrapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Rājēndrachōḷa: year 12: 1257-58 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription may be assigned to c. 13th century on grounds of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It records an order for the tax to be collected from the <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> and <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi</hi> lands from the month of Āḍi in the above year. The boundaries of such lands were demarked and the document concerning this was attested by <hi rend="italic">mudal-kaṇakku</hi> Kiḻakkuḍaiyān Tirujñānasamba[nda*]ruḍaiyān, Tribhuvanavīravēḷan and others.</p>						

						</summary>
